    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 27, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-27",
    "tags": ["GPT-5.5", "Biosecurity", "Privacy Filter", "NVIDIA Rubin", "Claude Mythos"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 27, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 OpenAI launched GPT-5.5 and immediately put a bounty on breaking it\n\nNothing says confidence like shipping the flagship model and then paying specialists to try to make it misbehave.\n\n- **The release:** OpenAI launched GPT-5.5 on April 23, said it hits 82.7% on Terminal-Bench 2.0 and 58.6% on SWE-Bench Pro, and priced the API at $5 per 1M input tokens and $30 per 1M output tokens when API access opened on April 24.\n- **The safety stunt:** the same day, OpenAI opened a GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty that offers $25,000 for the first universal jailbreak to clear all five bio safety questions, with applications open through June 22 and testing scheduled from April 28 to July 27.\n\n*Frontier releases now come with benchmarks, pricing, and a live stress test. Product marketing has become a contact sport.*\n\n**Sources:** [Introducing GPT-5.5](https://openai.com/index/introducing-gpt-5-5/) | [GPT-5.5 Bio Bug Bounty](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-bio-bug-bounty/)\n\n---\n\n## 🔒 OpenAI just open-sourced a privacy bouncer with a very specific job\n\nThe industry spent years leaking data into logs and training pipelines. So now we get a dedicated cleanup crew.\n\n- **What shipped:** OpenAI released Privacy Filter on April 22 as an open-weight model for detecting and redacting PII in text, with 1.5B total parameters, 50M active parameters, and support for up to 128,000 tokens.\n- **Why teams will care:** OpenAI says the model can run locally and reached 97.43% F1 on a corrected PII-Masking-300k benchmark, while covering eight label types including private dates, account numbers, and secrets such as API keys.\n\n*The hottest AI product category might briefly be \"please stop pasting private stuff into everything.\" Fair enough.*\n\n**Sources:** [Introducing OpenAI Privacy Filter](https://openai.com/index/introducing-openai-privacy-filter/) | [OpenAI Privacy Filter on Hugging Face](https://huggingface.co/openai/privacy-filter)\n\n---\n\n## ☁️ NVIDIA and Google Cloud are selling a robot-industrial complex by the rack\n\nCloud vendors no longer pitch servers. They pitch civilization-scale simulation boxes with a side of humanoids.\n\n- **The hardware flex:** NVIDIA and Google Cloud said on April 22 that new A5X bare-metal instances built on Vera Rubin can scale to nearly 1 million Rubin GPUs, with up to 10x lower inference cost per token and 10x higher token throughput per megawatt than the prior generation.\n- **The physical AI angle:** the stack also pulls in Gemini on Google Distributed Cloud, confidential Blackwell VMs, Isaac Sim, Omniverse libraries, and Cosmos Reason 2 so customers can train digital twins, robotics workflows, and vision agents before deployment.\n\n*The cloud is now a factory, the factory is now a simulator, and the simulator is apparently the economy.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA and Google Cloud Collaborate to Advance Agentic and Physical AI](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/google-cloud-agentic-physical-ai-factories/) | [NVIDIA and Partners Showcase the Future of AI-Driven Manufacturing at Hannover Messe 2026](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/ai-manufacturing-hannover-messe/)\n\n---\n\n## 🕳️ Anthropic's cyber wunderkind already found the wrong early adopters\n\nProject Glasswing was supposed to give trusted defenders a head start. The internet, naturally, interpreted that as a challenge.\n\n- **The setup:** Anthropic launched Project Glasswing on April 7 with Claude Mythos Preview, 12 named launch partners, access for more than 40 additional infrastructure organizations, up to $100 million in usage credits, and $4 million in donations to open-source security groups.\n- **The problem:** on April 21, TechCrunch reported that unauthorized users had gained access to Mythos through a third-party vendor environment, undercutting Anthropic's core pitch that restricted rollout would keep a powerful cyber model inside the velvet rope.\n\n*Elite access programs keep discovering the same timeless truth: the weakest link also gets an account.*\n\n**Sources:** [Project Glasswing](https://www.anthropic.com/project/glasswing) | [Unauthorized group has gained access to Anthropic's exclusive cyber tool Mythos, report claims](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/21/unauthorized-group-gained-access-anthropic-cyber-tool-mythos/)"
  }
]
